Peru October Trade Surplus Widens on Metal Price Gains

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-12-12T16:17:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-12/peru-october-trade-surplus-widens-on-metal-price-gains-1-.html
Peru ’s  trade  surplus widened in
October as rising gold and copper prices spurred export growth.  The Andean country had a trade surplus of $672 million in
October, compared with a $505 million surplus a year earlier,
the country’s National Statistics Institute said today in an e-
mailed report.  Exports rose 20 percent to $3.73 billion from a year ago,
the agency said. Imports climbed 18 percent to $3.06 billion,
led by demand for cars, televisions and mobile phones.  Metals accounted for 60 percent of Peru’s exports in
October.  The sol weakened 0.2 percent to 2.7015 per dollar at 11:11
a.m. Lima time from 2.6955 on Dec. 9.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
